title.narrative: Information technology, supply, logistics and administration to effectively support country operations.

description.narrative: Effective management of human resources was maintained, with increased recruitments, improved efficiency, enhanced business partnerships and staff empowerment through knowledge management initiatives and information sharing. The gender balance slightly decreased from 37 per cent in 2019 to 39 per cent in 2021. Priorities were reset to effectively support programme delivery needs during the COVID-19 pandemic. Simplified procedures and special measures were applied to fast-track recruitment and administer benefits and entitlements during the pandemic. Staff well-being initiatives focussing on stress management, staff capacity development and continuous learning were implemented. ; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2022
